Generic single-database configuration.
 Donation Management CLI

A Python-based command-line application that allows users to manage donors, causes, and donations for fundraising campaigns. It supports adding new donors, making donations, and tracking the progress of each cause.



 Features

-  List all fundraising causes with real-time progress
-  List all registered donors with total donation amounts
-  View all donations for a specific cause
-  Make a new donation (create or use existing donor)
-  Add new causes with fundraising goals
-  Data persisted using SQLite and SQLAlchemy ORM

---

Technologies Used

- Python 
- SQLAlchemy– ORM for database interaction
- SQLite – Lightweight file-based database

---

 Project Structure

donation-management-cli/
├── helpers.py # CLI logic for managing donors, causes, and donations
├── main.py # Entry point for the CLI menu
├── models.py # SQLAlchemy models for Donor, Cause, and Donation
├── seed.py # Sets up and seeds the database with initial data
├── lib/
│ └── db/
│ └── donations.db # SQLite database file (created automatically)